snippet: The unsportsmanlike conduct penalty Washington Redskins tight end Vernon Davis drew after a TD for shooting the football at the goalpost like a basketball at a rim is precisely why people joke that "NFL" stands for "No Fun League."...
lead_paragraph: The unsportsmanlike conduct penalty Washington Redskins tight end Vernon Davis drew after a TD for shooting the football at the goalpost like a basketball at a rim is precisely why people joke that "NFL" stands for "No Fun League."

headline.main: ICYMI in NFL's Week 6: Can't Celebrate in 'No Fun League'
